						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Local Chief Chokkaliṅga Nāyaka. Paridāvi, Vaigāsi 23 = c. 17th-18th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>One Veṅgaḷa-nāyakka who was a <hi rend="italic">pradhāni</hi> of Kāraveṭṭi-nāyakka Bommu-nāyakka made a <hi rend="italic">chattiram</hi> (feeding house) at Karuvūr for brāhmaṇa pilgrims. He gave some land in some villages lying north of Karuvūr for maintaining the <hi rend="italic">chattiram.</hi></p>						

